## Authority (one source each)

| Data | Owner |
|------|-------|
| Persistent project | `ProjectDocument` |
| Workspace (scene, selection, tools, camera) | `EditorState` |
| Layout/filters only | `EditorUiState` or panel-local state |
| Runtime during Play | `PlaySession` |
| Loaded textures | `TextureCache` (derived, never authoritative) |

## Mutation flow

```
UI/SceneView â†’ Intent (workspace) or Command (persistent/undo)
  â†’ EditorCoordinator â†’ ProjectDocument â†’ DomainChange â†’ targeted invalidation
```

- RmlUi never mutates `ProjectDocument` directly.
- Input buffers commit on Enter/blur only when valid and changed.
- No polling, sync service, event bus, or `RefreshAll()` per frame.

## Edit / Play

- Start Play: materialize once from `ProjectDocument`; runtime never reads document per frame.
- During Play: authoring Commands blocked at coordinator (UI disable is affordance only).
- Stop: destroy `PlaySession`; no reverse-sync to authoring.

## Module boundaries (forbidden)

- `artcade-editor-core` â†’ no RmlUi, Raylib, concrete filesystem.
- Renderer / `SceneView` â†’ no `ProjectDocument`; consume `SceneFrameSnapshot` only.
- Commands â†’ no `Rml::Element`, no UI types.

